creator: Flatirontek LLC
descriptionHtml:
Vybit is a nerdy utility that creates custom sound alerts for specific Internet events. It is basically a mashup between Internet services that support outbound webhooks with the library of sounds at freesound.org.

Vybit is awesome because you can be alerted to things happening that are important to you by sounds that YOU CHOOSE! Sure, our devices make generic sounds to notify us of things, but then we have to look down and visually process the message to get the details. With Vybit you will know exactly what the sound means because YOU CHOOSE THE SOUND! Humans can recognize thousands of distinct sounds. The purpose of Vybit is to take advantage of this capability. To get a little nerdier, each individual sound, i.e., VIBE, that you choose is connected to a specific event, or BIT, of information, ergo, Vybit! :)

To learn how to get started with Vybit either install this app and review the docs under PROFILE or visit https://www.vybit.net.
descriptionShort: Vybit is a notification app that uses custom sounds for specific digital events.

appDetails.recentChangesHtml: Bug fix introduced on last release. Apologies. Please return to your libations.

title: Vybit

creator: Flatirontek LLC
descriptionHtml:
Vybit sends distinct, custom sound notifications to your under-utilized ears so that your over-worked eyes can get a break! Sure, our devices already make app-generic notification sounds, but then we have to grab our phone and look down to process the details.

With Vybit you will know EXACTLY what the sound means because YOU CHOOSE THE SOUND from thousands of quality, searchable sounds.

Vybs (vibes) are triggered by any Internet service that supports outgoing webhooks, e.g., IFTTT and Zapier. DevOps folks can easily integrate Vybit into RMMs or directly curl/wget vybs from closer to the metal. Vybs can also be shared, e.g., with your spouse to let him/her know you are on your way home, with your team to alert them that the database server just went kaput, or with your customers to announce a new product release.

Humans can recognize thousands of distinct sounds. The purpose of Vybit is to take advantage of this capability. Each individual sound, i.e., VIBE, that you choose is connected to a specific event, or "BIT" of information, ergo, Vybit! :)

To learn how to get started with Vybit install this app and review the documentation at https://www.vybit.net/#getting_started.
descriptionShort: Create custom sound notifications from thousands of searchable sounds.
